---

<IndividualPageLayout
    title={seoTitle}
    description={seoDescription}
    schema={pageSchema}
    pageTitle={pageTitle}
    heroImage="/oscar/media/die-casting-investment-casting-forging-cnc-high-precision-machining-title-bar-2.jpg"
    heroImageAlt="Forged Inconel 718 rings and high-performance industrial components"
    faqSectionTitle="Frequently Asked Questions: Sand Casting"
    faqItems={faqs}
    ctaTitle="Request Quote For Sand Casting"
    ctaDescription=""
    sourcesTitle="Sources"
    sourcesList={sources}
    resourcesTitle="Our Internal Resources for Die Casting, Investment casting, Forging and Sand Casting"
    resourcesList={internalResources}
>

    <div slot="full-width" class="individual-content">

        <section id="overview">
            <div class="content-container">
                
                <h2>Sand Casting: Large-Scale, Cost-Effective Metal Manufacturing</h2>

                <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center mt-6">
                    <div>
                        <p>
                            ForceBeyond is a premier global supplier of high-quality sand cast components. As one of the oldest and most versatile metal manufacturing processes, sand casting remains the absolute standard for producing massive, heavy-duty components and complex geometries at an incredibly cost-effective price point.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Operating under a strict ISO 9001:2015 quality management system, our high-capacity foundries utilize both automated green sand lines (for high-volume production) and precise resin/no-bake sand molding (for massive, low-volume parts). From lightweight aluminum engine blocks to heavy-duty ductile iron pump housings, we deliver fully machined, heat-treated, and coated castings tailored exactly to your engineering requirements.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="relative">
                        <div class="overflow-hidden">
                            <img
                                src="/oscar/media/custom-metal-sand-casting-parts-housings-flanges-4k.webp"
                                alt="Custom metal sand casting parts, including pump housings, flanges, brackets, threaded fittings, and industrial components on a white background."
                                class="w-full h-auto object-cover hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="technical-capabilities">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Technical Capabilities: Sand Casting Materials</h2>
                <p>
                    The sand casting process is uniquely capable of pouring nearly any commercial alloy. ForceBeyond specializes in the heavy-duty ferrous metals and lightweight aluminum alloys most demanded by the industrial, automotive, and energy sectors.
                </p>
                <div class="content-table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="col">Material Category</th>
                                <th scope="col">Common Grades Poured</th>
                                <th scope="col">Key Features & Optimal Applications</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>

                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Ductile Iron</th>
                                <td>ASTM A536 (60-40-18, 65-45-12, 80-55-06)</td>
                                <td>Contains nodular graphite, providing the castability of iron with the tensile strength and toughness of steel. Ideal for heavy-duty automotive axles, gears, and suspension components.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Gray Iron</th>
                                <td>ASTM A48 (Class 20, 30, 40)</td>
                                <td>Excellent vibration dampening and thermal conductivity. Cost-effective and highly machinable. Used heavily for machine tool bases, engine blocks, and brake rotors.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Carbon & Alloy Steel</th>
                                <td>WCB, 1020, 1045, 4140</td>
                                <td>Massive strength and impact resistance. Mandatory for high-stress heavy machinery linkages, massive valve bodies, and structural mining equipment.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Aluminum Alloys</th>
                                <td>A356-T6, 319, 355</td>
                                <td>Excellent strength-to-weight ratio and corrosion resistance. Frequently used for aerospace components, lightweight automotive transmission housings, and complex marine impellers.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div> 
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="why-partner">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Why Partner with ForceBeyond for Sand Casting?</h2>
                <p>
                    When parts are incredibly large, have massive cross-sections, or require complex internal geometries, sand casting frequently outperforms forging and die casting.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Massive Size & Weight Capacity:</strong> Sand casting is not constrained by the physical size of a die casting machine or forging press. We can pour components weighing from just a few pounds up to several tons, making it the only viable process for massive industrial hardware.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Low Tooling Costs:</strong> The patterns (tools) used to create the sand molds are typically made from wood, polyurethane, or aluminum. This makes sand casting tooling significantly cheaper and faster to produce than the hardened steel dies required for die casting or forging.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Complex Internal Coring:</strong> By placing baked sand cores inside the main mold, we can cast highly intricate internal cavities, fluid passages, and volutes (such as those found in pump housings and engine blocks) that would be impossible to CNC machine.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Rapid Prototyping to High-Volume:</strong> Using temporary wood patterns or 3D-printed sand molds, we can rapidly produce prototypes. Once the design is locked, we can transition the part to hard aluminum tooling on our automated green sand lines for high-volume, repeatable production.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="molding-process">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>The Sand Casting Process: Green Sand vs. Resin Sand</h2>

                <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center mt-6">
                    <div>
                        <p>
                            ForceBeyond utilizes the most appropriate molding technology based on the size, surface finish, and volume requirements of your project.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Green Sand Molding:</strong> A mixture of sand, clay, and water (it is called "green" because it contains moisture, not because of its color). It is highly cost-effective, easily recyclable, and ideal for automated, high-volume production runs of small to medium-sized parts.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Resin (No-Bake) Sand Molding:</strong> The sand is mixed with a chemical resin that hardens at room temperature. This creates an extremely rigid mold that yields tighter dimensional tolerances, a smoother surface finish, and the structural strength necessary to cast massive, multi-ton components.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="relative">
                        <div class="overflow-hidden">
                            <img
                                src="/oscar/media/sand-cast-threaded-flange-mounting-housing-4k.webp"
                                alt="Sand-cast metal threaded flange housing with three mounting holes and reinforced ribs on a white background."
                                class="w-full h-auto object-cover hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="tier-1-5-integration">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Tier-1.5 Integration: Cast, Machine & Finish Solutions</h2>
                <p>
                    Because sand castings have looser as-cast tolerances and rougher surface finishes than investment castings, secondary machining is almost always required. ForceBeyond operates a Tier-1.5 model, providing all necessary finishing under one roof.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Our In-House Secondary Operations Include:</strong>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Heavy CNC Machining:</strong> Large-envelope vertical turning lathes (VTLs) and horizontal boring mills to hit exact print tolerances on massive iron and steel castings.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Advanced Heat Treatment:</strong> Stress relieving (crucial for large iron castings), Normalizing, Annealing, and the T6 heat treatment process (solution treating and artificial aging) to maximize the strength of A356 aluminum.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Surface Preparation & Coating:</strong> Shot blasting to remove all molding sand, followed by rust-preventative coatings, powder coating, painting, or e-coating.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Rigorous NDT:</strong> Magnetic Particle Inspection (MPI) and Ultrasonic Testing (UT) to guarantee the internal soundness of heavy structural parts.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="certified-applications">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Certified Sand Casting Applications</h2>
                <p>
                    Our high-capacity foundry network supplies heavy-duty sand castings to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Heavy Machinery & Agriculture:</strong> Tractor weights, excavator linkages, gearboxes, and massive structural frames.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Pumps & Fluid Control:</strong> Massive WCB steel valve bodies, ductile iron pump volutes, and multi-stage impellers.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Automotive & Commercial Vehicles:</strong> Engine blocks, cylinder heads, differential housings, and brake calipers.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Energy & Power Generation:</strong> Wind turbine hubs, heavy-duty compressor housings, and gas turbine structural bases.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>
</IndividualPageLayout>